The N2 near Plettenberg Bay in the Western Cape remains closed following overnight protests. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The N2 near Plettenberg Bay in the Western Cape remains closed following overnight protests. READ: Border Police confiscate counterfeit goods worth millions At least 71 people have been arrested in connection with the demonstrations. Regional police spokesperson Chris Spies says the situation remains tense in the area with sporadic attacks on law enforcement authorities by protestors. “Police action will continue in order for us to normalise the situation there,” Spies said. “We have also brought in extra policemen, reinforcements from Cape Town and Paarl, in particular, public order police members to assist us to restore law and order in Plettenberg Bay.”